description: Reblozyl (luspatercept) is a first-in-class erythroid maturation agent (EMA) indicated for the treatment of anemia in adult patients with beta thalassemia who require regular red blood cell (RBC) transfusions and in adult patients with very low- to intermediate-risk myelodysplastic syndromes (MDS)-associated anemia who have ring sideroblasts and require RBC transfusions.
